column2: Migrated from EPA STORET Legacy Database- originally reported by Wisconsin DNR
Ice on 11/20/86- ice off 4/8/87- aerator in operation until 4-13-87.
Water is clear- lake is so full of algae you can't see through it.
All summer the transparency depth was 2 feet due to algae and plankton.
Loaded w/ algae all of august
Lots of algae last 2 weeks.- in June lake was clear- 8' visibility
Water clear but couldn't see through floating green algae.
The month of august was very poor in water quality.
Algae and weeds floating in the water.
Dark skies- storm approaching- NW wind 5 mph- 60 degree temp.- algae along shoreline- no activity.
Clear weather- 5 mph NW wind- 75 degree temp.- rained yesterday- 2 small boats on lake- algae bloom along east shoreline.
Some green algae- partly cloudy- 75 mph SW wind- 75 degrees- thunderstorms + rain yesterday- 1 fishing + 1 speed boat on water.
Clear skies- minor algae- 4 mph NW wind- 75 degrees temp.- one fishing boat on water.
Clear skies- calm to 6 mph gust of wind out of southwest.  Minor algae problem. 80 degrees temp.- 4 fishing boats- one ski boat very active- 1 paddle boat on water.
Partly cloudy skies- calm 5 mph SW winds.  Substantial algae- 80 degrees temp.- one fishing boat- thunderstorm this morning.
Overcast skies- calm NW winds.  Major algae in water- nothing floating on top.  70 degree temp.  Rain last night + this morning.  No boat activity.

Overcast skies- calm NW winds.  Major very fine green algae in water.  Very little algae floating on top.  70 degree temp.  Thunderstorm-rain yesterday.  3 ski boats- one pontoon- 1 fishing boat on water.
Clear skies- 10 mph S wind.  70 degree temp.- little boat activity- 1 pontoon- 1 ski boat.
Clear skies- SW wind calm to 7 mph.  More normal wind the past 2 days.  72 degree temp.  Little boat activity- 1 fishing boat- some algae floating along shoreline.
Clear skies SW wind calm- 3 mph- 58 degrees- little boat activity- very little algae present.
Partly cloudy-northwest wind 5 mph-temp. 60 degrees.  Ice off April 17th 1995.  Ice on November 23 1994.  One fishing boat - no algae.
Clear skies-5 to 10 mph NW wind-temp. 64 degrees-no algae-one fish boat on water-rain  2 days ago .5"-lots of wind past 3 days.
Partly cloudy-0 to 5 mph SW wind- temp. 70 degrees.  Rain over the weekend.  Algae bloom 1 day after rain.  Heavy boat activity over weekend-wed/little today.
Cloudy-calm-5 mph- S wind- temp. 58 degrees- cold + rainy yesterday- little boat activity- algae present in the water-none on top.
Clear to partly cloudy skies 3-5 mph south wind.  Temp. 85 degrees- algae present in water-none on top.  More than usual boat traffic past week.  No rain past week.

Aerator turned on 6/24 2: 00 p.m.  Clear to partly cloudy skies 0-5 mph SW wind.  Thunderstorms yesterday about 3/8" rain.  Temp. 76 degrees.  Fine algae present in water large clumps of weeds floating on top.

Aerator turned on 6/24 2: 00 p.m.  Clear to partly cloudy skies 0-5 mph SW wind.  Thunderstorms yesterday about 3/8" rain.  Temp. 76 degrees.  Fine algae present in water large clumps of weeds floating on top.
Clear skies- windy 5-10 mph NW wind- 70 degree temp.  Rain yesterday- aerator off noon today.  Algae present in water- none on top.
Clear skies- 10 mph NW wind- lots of rain- 4.5" past week. 65 degree temp.- windy.  Today + yesterday little boat activity.
Clear calm-3 mph NW wind- 62 degrees temp.  One fishing boat on water.  Algae present in water-none on top.
Clear skies- 7 mph NW wind- 48 degrees temp- no boat activity.  No algae present on water- very little in water.
Clear skies- 5 mph SW wind- 25 degree temp.- one boat in water.  No algae present on surface- very little in water.
DEEP HOLE - 6FT INTEGRATED SAMPLE     cloudy/sun   Possible showers
DEEP HOLE - 6FT INTEGRATED SAMPLE     83 Degrees- 10 MPH Wind- Sunny
DEEP HOLE - 6FT INTEGRATED SAMPLE     65F- 5mph wind- sunny
partly cloudy- moderate wind- air temperature 57 degrees
air temp 72 degrees.  Clear skies. Light breeze. Light boat traffic--fisherman. Observed 1 loon.
Thought I would get out between rain showers.  No such luck.  Poured when I reached the deep hole.  Skies mostly overcast. Air temp 63 degrees. Moderate wind. Moderate boat traffic.
overcast and windy--on/off rain  observed only one fishing boat--air temp 59 degrees
Mostly sunny.  Moderate breeze. Very light boat traffic. Shoreline is gross.
Mostly sunny with few clouds. Light breeze.  One loon seen.
Partly cloudy- 72 degrees with light breeze.  No boat traffic.
Mostly cloudy- 64 degrees.  Moderate wind.  Rain by the time I reached the deep hole. Saw one fishing boat.
Beautiful day.  Partly cloudy- moderate wind 75 degree air temp. No boat traffic.
Windy and 74 degrees.  Several fishing boats. 1 loon. Mostly cloudy.
Beautiful sunny day.  Light breeze. 71 degrees.  No boat traffic.
70 degrees  Mostly sunny- moderate breeze. Algae along shoreline.  1 loon.  No boat traffic
Clear skies- no boat traffic on lake. Ken Kroiss- Joe Burger- Bonnie Szydel
Sunny and 67 degrees.  Slight breeze. No  boat traffic.
Cloudy- moderate breeze- 55 degrees.  Beautiful fall color.  No boat traffic.
Mostly cloudy 37 degrees  Moderate northerly breeze.  Observed 1 loon(??)  Saw 2 yesterday
Mostly cloudy and 47 degrees. Moderate breeze. Few raindrops.  Saw 1 kayaker.  No other boat traffic
Gorgeous day.  Temp is 72 degrees. Heavy boat traffic as it is the holiday "weekend".  First time rain and deep cloud cover haven't prevented a reading.

Beautiful day. 74 degrees. Mostly sunny. Slight breeze. Few boats.  Fisherman were catching some large mouth bass. Great excitement--observed a family of 4 loons.  Looked like they were teaching the young ones.
80 degrees. Beautiful day. Mostly sunny. Moderate breeze to light wind. One jet ski. 2 loons.
74 degrees Partly cloudy Light breeze Few boats
62 degrees- mostly cloudy- light wind- 2 fishing boats- 1 canoe and 1 kayak
67 degrees- light breeze- partly cloudy- no boat traffic- gross swirls of blue green algae

53 degrees brisk N wind sun-clouds-rain we have it all today Made it out in a window of sun/clouds. Water quality greatly improved from 2 days ago.  The wind is blowing the algae elsewhere. No boat traffic.
72 degrees Moderate wind from the south. Partly cloudy. Quiet day on the lake. Heard one boat on the water.
54 degrees. Mostly cloudy. Windy. 2 fishing boats.
45 degrees- windy- sunny- cloudy- rain showers crazy day.
84 degrees and sunny.  Heavy holiday boat traffic.  Mosquitoes are abundant.  Swallowtail butterflies and bumblebees were busy on the chokecherry blossoms.  Beautiful day to be on the water.
53 degrees sunny day with a slight breeze.  No boat traffic today.
68 degrees. Light breeze. several fishing boats.
64 degrees. Light Breeze. No boat traffic. One loon.
69 degrees. Cloudless sky. Several boats on the water.  Tree chopped down near my pier by ???? suspect fisherman who got a lure stuck.  :( :(  Quite disgusting.

Calm 66 degrees. Several fishing boats. Clear skies. Two pair of loons-one pair surfaced directly in front of me at the reading location. Algae growth is evident. Some scum on surface that appears to be plant material.
70 degrees.  Little or no breeze. 1 fishing boat.  Lake is GROSS!
77 degrees. Light southerly breeze.  Lake is totally quiet--no boats about.
74 degrees very windy- few clouds- only one boat seen.
72 degrees. Very windy. Mostly cloudy. 2 boats seen.
60 degrees. VERY WINDY!! Partial cloud cover. 1 boat.
47 degrees. Slight breeze. Mostly cloudy.  Few ducks.
